---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Accessibility Statement"
  description="Our commitment to web accessibility and how we ensure our website is usable by everyone, including people with disabilities."
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <h1>Accessibility Statement</h1>
      
      <p class="lead">
        Courses & Careers is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities. 
        We are continually improving the user experience for everyone and applying the relevant accessibility standards.
      </p>

      <h2>Our Commitment</h2>
      <p>
        We are dedicated to providing a website that is accessible to the widest possible audience, 
        regardless of technology or ability. We aim to comply with the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.2 
        Level AA standards and to continuously improve accessibility throughout our website.
      </p>

      <h2>Accessibility Standards</h2>
      <p>
        This website strives to conform to the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.2 Level AA. 
        These guidelines explain how to make web content more accessible for people with disabilities and 
        user-friendly for everyone.
      </p>

      <h2>Measures We Have Taken</h2>
      <p>We have implemented the following accessibility measures:</p>
      
      <h3>Navigation and Structure</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Logical heading hierarchy (H1, H2, H3, etc.)</li>
        <li>Skip links to main content</li>
        <li>Consistent navigation structure</li>
        <li>Clear page titles and meta descriptions</li>
        <li>Breadcrumb navigation where appropriate</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Content and Media</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Alt text for all informative images</li>
        <li>Captions and transcripts for video content</li>
        <li>Descriptive link text</li>
        <li>Clear and simple language</li>
        <li>Proper color contrast ratios (minimum 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Keyboard Navigation</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>All interactive elements accessible via keyboard</li>
        <li>Visible focus indicators</li>
        <li>Logical tab order</li>
        <li>Keyboard shortcuts where appropriate</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Forms and Interactive Elements</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Proper form labels and instructions</li>
        <li>Clear error messages and validation</li>
        <li>Required fields clearly marked</li>
        <li>Accessible form controls and buttons</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Screen Reader Support</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Semantic HTML markup</li>
        <li>ARIA labels and roles where needed</li>
        <li>Live regions for dynamic content updates</li>
        <li>Screen reader-friendly table headers</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Accessibility Features</h2>
      <p>Our website includes the following accessibility features:</p>
      
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Responsive Design:</strong> Works on all devices and screen sizes</li>
        <li><strong>High Contrast Support:</strong> Adapts to high contrast mode preferences</li>
        <li><strong>Reduced Motion:</strong> Respects users' motion preferences</li>
        <li><strong>Font Size:</strong> Can be increased up to 200% without loss of functionality</li>
        <li><strong>Color Independence:</strong> Information is not conveyed by color alone</li>
        <li><strong>Focus Management:</strong> Proper focus handling for modal dialogs and dynamic content</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Assistive Technologies</h2>
      <p>
        Our website has been tested with the following assistive technologies and browsers:
      </p>
      
      <ul>
        <li>JAWS (Windows)</li>
        <li>NVDA (Windows)</li>
        <li>VoiceOver (macOS/iOS)</li>
        <li>Dragon NaturallySpeaking (Windows)</li>
        <li>Keyboard-only navigation</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Browser Compatibility</h2>
      <p>
        We test our website regularly on the following browsers and assistive technology combinations:
      </p>
      
      <ul>
        <li>Chrome with JAWS and NVDA</li>
        <li>Firefox with JAWS and NVDA</li>
        <li>Safari with VoiceOver</li>
        <li>Edge with JAWS and NVDA</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Known Limitations</h2>
      <p>
        While we strive for full accessibility, there may be some limitations. We are actively working to address:
      </p>
      
      <ul>
        <li>Third-party embedded content that may not be fully accessible</li>
        <li>Legacy PDF documents (we are working to make these accessible)</li>
        <li>Complex interactive elements that may require additional keyboard instructions</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Feedback and Contact</h2>
      <p>
        We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of our website. If you encounter any accessibility 
        barriers or have suggestions for improvement, please contact us:
      </p>
      
      <div class="contact-info">
        <p>
          <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:accessibility@courses-careers.com">accessibility@courses-careers.com</a><br>
          <strong>Phone:</strong> <a href="tel:+1-555-123-4567">+1 (555) 123-4567</a><br>
          <strong>Mail:</strong> Courses & Careers, Accessibility Team<br>
          123 Education Street, Learning City, LC 12345
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <p>
        We aim to respond to accessibility feedback within 2 business days and will work with you to 
        resolve any issues promptly.
      </p>

      <h2>Accessibility Assessment</h2>
      <p>
        This website has been evaluated for accessibility compliance by both automated testing tools 
        and manual review. We use the following tools and methods:
      </p>
      
      <ul>
        <li>Automated accessibility testing with axe-core</li>
        <li>Manual keyboard navigation testing</li>
        <li>Screen reader testing with multiple tools</li>
        <li>Color contrast analysis</li>
        <li>Focus management verification</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Ongoing Improvements</h2>
      <p>
        Accessibility is an ongoing effort. We regularly:
      </p>
      
      <ul>
        <li>Review and update content for accessibility</li>
        <li>Train our team on accessibility best practices</li>
        <li>Monitor for accessibility issues and user feedback</li>
        <li>Update our accessibility statement as we make improvements</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Additional Resources</h2>
      <p>
        For more information about web accessibility, visit:
      </p>
      
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Web Accessibility Initiative (WAI)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.ada.gov/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://webaim.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">WebAIM</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Legal Compliance</h2>
      <p>
        This website aims to comply with:
      </p>
      
      <ul>
        <li>Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA)</li>
        <li>Section 508 of the Rehabilitation Act</li>
        <li>Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.2 Level AA</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="last-updated">
        <strong>Last Updated:</strong> <time datetime="2024-01-15">January 15, 2024</time>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
